parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake booster can cause a loss of power-assisted braking, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes make a loud clunking noise
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the caliper mounting hardware can cause the caliper to detach, leading to a loss of braking capability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes make a loud clunking noise
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the caliper becomes detached from the rotor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OptiSpark distributor can cause the engine to misfire, backfire, and stall, leading to a potential safety hazard, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine misses
backfires
and stalls continuously after warming up
engine runs rough
engine skips and operates as though it is on fewer cylinders.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission malfunction can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates at high speed without driver input
the throttle sticks in an open position
the braking system is inoperative
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure - Metal Filings in Valve Body
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of metal filings in the valve body of the transmission can cause the governor to stay wide open, leading to unintended acceleration and loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward unexpectedly
the transmission malfunctions
metal filings are present in the valve body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The speedometer malfunction can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's actual speed, potentially leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer continues to read at a certain speed although the car is at a full stop
incorrect speed readings on the speedometer.
